Description of incident: North East Medical Services notified patients of a security breach when an employees laptop was stolen from the trunk of the employees car. The information compromised included names, dates of birth, gender, contact information, payer/insurer and limited personal health information. According to the medical office no Social Security number or credit card information or actual medical record was involved. More Information: http://oag.ca.gov/ecrime/databreach/reports/sb24-57240
